Christopher Danjuma, coach of the national under-20 women football team, says they are ready for their return leg to encounter with Senegal in the 2022 FIFA Under-20 Women’s World Cup qualifiers. Danjuma told the News Agency of Nigeria (NAN) in Benin on Thursday that the Falconets have mapped out a strategy on how to take the game beyond their opponents. NAN reports that the Nigerian side who host Senegal on Saturday at the Samuel Ogbemudia Stadium in Benin had won the first leg fixture 3-1 away about a fortnight ago.   Eunisell sponsorship aided our superb performance – Rivers…     Super Eagles hit Ghana for World Cup play off     Die to beat Super Eagles, officials urge Black Stars   Danjuma said his team trained on Thursday morning and would hopefully conclude their training sessions for the match on Friday at the venue of the match. “Thankfully, we have no injury scare and the girls are ready for the game. Our first leg fixture gave us an opportunity to know the Senegalese better. So, we are prepared and ready to go.” The Falconets had arrived in Benin on Wednesday for the final phase of their preparation for the match.(NAN)